-- Belarus Agrees to Join Russian-Kazakhstan Customs Union, Vedomosti Reports
-- Anastasia Ustinova
-- 2010-07-05T04:37:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/belarus-agrees-to-join-russian-kazakhstan-customs-union-vedomosti-reports.html

          
          
             Belarus President Aleksandr
Lukashenko dropped his opposition to joining a customs union
with Russia and Kazakhstan after his country reached an
agreement on gas-trasnit fees with Moscow-based OAO Gazprom,
Vedomosti reported.  
 Lukashenko will dicuss the details of joining the union
with his Russian and Kazakh counterparts, Dmitry Medvedev and
Nursaltan Nazarbayev in the Kazakh capital Astana today, the
Moscow-based newspaper said, citing the Belarus government.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
